15:46.195 --> 15:48.237
MY, THAT'S A LOVELY BLENDER.

15:48.405 --> 15:49.280
THIS IS STUPID.

15:49.448 --> 15:52.325
RED...

15:52.493 --> 15:55.244
WELL, IT'S GOT STAINLESS STEEL
ROTOR BLADES

15:55.412 --> 15:56.412
SO IT CAN CRUSH ICE,

15:56.580 --> 15:58.539
WHICH IS WHY I KEEP IT
OUT HERE AT THE BAR,

15:58.707 --> 16:01.584
UM... AND IT HAS THE HIGHEST
WATTAGE THAT YOU CAN GET

16:01.752 --> 16:03.419
WITHOUT MOVING UP
TO THE INDUSTRIAL MODEL

16:03.587 --> 16:05.880
WHICH WOULD COST YOU
TWICE AS MUCH.

16:06.674 --> 16:08.633
WELL, NOW, SEE, WE HAVE HAD
THIS BLENDER ALL THESE YEARS,

16:08.801 --> 16:11.177
AND I NEVER KNEW
THAT'S WHY WE BOUGHT IT.

16:11.345 --> 16:11.886
YOU DIDN'T KNOW THAT?

16:12.054 --> 16:14.597
HOW COULD YOU
NOT KNOW THAT?!

16:14.765 --> 16:16.849
RED, EVERYBODY
DOESN'T RESEARCH EVERY PRODUCT

16:17.017 --> 16:18.643
BEFORE THEY BUY IT.

16:18.811 --> 16:20.937
WELL, THEN,
THEY'RE DUMB ASSES.

16:22.272 --> 16:23.147
THAT'S RIGHT.

16:23.315 --> 16:27.860
AND THAT'S WHY THEY NEED YOU
TO TELL THEM WHAT TO BUY.

16:28.028 --> 16:29.028
HMM.

16:29.196 --> 16:31.030
[SNICKERS LOUDLY]

16:31.198 --> 16:34.701
I THINK YOU ARE JUST
TAILOR-MADE FOR THIS JOB.

16:34.868 --> 16:35.952
HECK, I GO
INTO BUY SOMETHING,

16:36.120 --> 16:39.330
ALL I KNOW
IS WHAT COLOR I WANT.

16:41.625 --> 16:44.419
YOU'RE ONE OF THEM!

16:45.379 --> 16:48.464
WELL, I THINK YOU SHOULD
BE NICE TO ME, RED,

16:48.632 --> 16:50.049
BECAUSE I THINK
I MIGHT BE INTERESTED

16:50.217 --> 16:52.760
IN PURCHASING A MATTRESS.

16:53.220 --> 16:56.556
KITTY, WE DON'T
EVEN SELL... OH!

17:03.647 --> 17:07.150
I MISS ERIC.

17:07.317 --> 17:09.152
WELL, YOU
STILL HAVE ME.

17:09.319 --> 17:11.779
IT'S NOT THE SAME,
JACKIE.

17:13.407 --> 17:14.699
I CAN TALK TO ERIC
ABOUT THINGS

17:14.867 --> 17:18.619
THAT I CAN'T
TALK ABOUT WITH YOU.

17:18.787 --> 17:20.913
OKAY, WELL, LIKE WHAT?

17:21.081 --> 17:22.623
WELL...

17:22.791 --> 17:25.501
FOR INSTANCE, THE ANNOYING
THINGS THAT YOU DO.

17:25.669 --> 17:27.545
MICHAEL!

17:27.713 --> 17:30.048
SEE?
I CAN'T TALK TO YOU!

17:32.342 --> 17:34.969
HEY, ERIC, HOW'S IT...

17:40.684 --> 17:44.145
SO WHAT'S EVERYONE
LOOKIN' AT?

17:44.313 --> 17:45.104
WHAT ARE WE LOOKIN
AT, MAN?

17:45.272 --> 17:46.522
WE HAVEN'T
SEEN YOU IN DAYS.

17:46.690 --> 17:47.273
OH, WHAT, HYDE?

17:47.441 --> 17:50.026
YOU HAD TO WALK ALL THE WAY
HOME FROM SCHOOL AGAIN?

17:50.194 --> 17:53.863
THAT'S NOT THE ONLY REASON
WE'RE UPSET WITH YOU.

17:54.031 --> 17:55.948
THAT'S MY ONLY REASON.

17:56.950 --> 17:58.659
I THOUGHT YOU
HAD ANOTHER REASON.

17:58.827 --> 18:01.037
NO. THAT'S PRETTY MUCH IT.

18:01.205 --> 18:03.081
WHERE'S BUDDY?

18:03.248 --> 18:03.873
OH, BUDDY.

18:04.041 --> 18:05.875
OH...

18:06.043 --> 18:08.211
OH, WELL,
BUDDY GOT...

18:08.378 --> 18:10.671
BUSY, SO...

18:12.049 --> 18:13.174
YEAH. I'M SURE
HE HAS A LOT TO DO.

18:13.342 --> 18:14.675
HE IS POPULAR.

18:14.843 --> 18:17.762
YEAH, AND SO
OBVIOUSLY GAY.

18:20.307 --> 18:22.892
